# Service Worker Cache Policy

- `data.json` and `heartbeat.json` must prioritize freshness (network-first).
- App shell files (`index.html`, `app.js`, helper JS, styles) must use a documented strategy and cache-bust plan.
- Any shell cache strategy change requires cache version bump in `docs/sw.js`.

## Deployment Safety

- Keep script/style cache-bust values (`?v=` or equivalent) coherent across pages.
- Preserve a clear stale-client recovery path (hard refresh/SW unregister guidance).
- Do not introduce cache behavior that can strand users on stale `app.js`.

## Verification

- Validate first-load and repeat-load behavior.
- Verify updated shell assets are fetched after deploy.
- Confirm `docs/sw.js` and HTML asset URLs are aligned.
